history.content:
The reserved seats were released on Aug 5. At this point, the reason that there are still open seats is because students are waitlisted for full lab and/or discussions and/or they have a time conflict. 

Please search for questions before asking. In the new system, in order to switch secondary sections you have to drop and re-add.

If you drop and re-add with an open lab and discussion, have no time conflict, and are not over your allowed units, you should be enrolled.

*Edit* Update: I ended up taking the leap and managed to rearrange my schedule to enroll in ee16a! I had to drop cs70, but I might have ended up dropping that course early in the semester anyway, and I hope that means one waitlisted cs70 student is now just as happy as I am!

I am currently number 48 on the waitlist for EE16a, and am wondering if reserved seats have been fully released yet (since I still see that there are open seats in the lecture, but according to calcentral the lecture is waitlisted).


If so, I see that there are open seats in some discussions and labs as well. Is there a way for me to switch the lab and discussions I am waitlisted for now, to the open ones? Is this my best bet for getting into the class, or should I just stay waitlisted for the TuesThurs 8AM discussion (Waitlist of 9) and Wed 8AM lab (Waitlist of 8)?

If I do this, I want to be sure I can get a seat, as I would switching to a lab that conflicts with CS70 lecture and would have to drop it as a result. 

Any advice for best ensuring I can enroll into the class? I phased 1 this class and I really want to be able to take it :)!
